# Stressar exported run bundle (`results/<run-name>/`)

Treat each **`<run-name>/`** directory as one benchmark run (one scenario + timestamp).

## Typical files

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `run_metadata.json` | Scenario label, replica counts, DB connection budget, proxy flags — use as run-level join key. |
| `replica-*/summary.json` | Per-replica aggregates: `runInfo` (SUT, workload, target Rps, duration, pool sizing), throughput, errors, latency percentiles, resource hints. |
| `report.md` | Human summary; cross-check numbers against JSON when automating. |
| `node_metrics/pg_metrics.csv` | DB-side time series (connections, commits, cache, checkpoints, …). |
| `node_metrics/db/db_proc_metrics.csv` | DB host process sampling. |
| `node_metrics/proxy/*_proc_metrics.csv` | Proxy host CPU/memory-style sampling (names vary by SUT). |
| `node_metrics/proxy/*_jvm_metrics.csv` | JVM/`jstat` sidecar where present (OJP runs). |
| `node_metrics/lb/*.csv` | Present for PgBouncer topology (HAProxy). |

## Conventions

- **`summary.json`:** `runInfo.instanceId` / `totalInstances` identify the replica; align with folder `replica-<id>/`.
- **Comparisons:** join runs on stable keys from `run_metadata.json` + `runInfo` (same `workload`, `loadMode`, comparable `targetRps` / phase) — see `stressar-docs/BENCHMARKING_GUIDE.md` for what “fair” comparison means in this study.
